steps.step: Heat the cooking oil in a pot.
Saute the ginger until fragrant.
Add the pork tenderloin, spleen and kidney. Cook until the meat changes color.
Add the garlic and onion. Continue sauteing until the onion slices appear translucent.
Pour in the broth. Season with fish sauce. Bring to the boil. Lower the heat, cover and simmer for 15 to 30 minutes.
Add the pork liver.
Pour in the pork blood. Bring to the boil.
Add more fish sauce, if needed. If using pepper, add it now. Lower the heat, cover and simmer for another 10 minutes.Turn off the heat.
Add the sili leaves, pressing them down into the broth. Cover and leave to wilt the leaves for a few minutes.
Serve the batchoy soup hot.

steps.step: Place lime juice, olive oil, garlic, salt, and oregano in a large resealable plastic bag. Shake sealed bag until ingredients are well mixed. Taste the marinade for tartness. If too tart, add a little more oil. Not enough zing, add more lime. The garlic and salt flavors should also be up front, yet not overpowering.
Place tenderloins in the bag, seal, and turn to coat. Marinate in the refrigerator for 2 to 5 hours.
Preheat grill for medium heat.
Lightly oil the grill grate, and discard marinade. Grill tenderloins for 20 to 30 minutes, turning once, or to desired doneness.

results.title: Easy zucchini and chicken breast casserole

steps.step: Slice the chicken breast fillets into thin slices. Season them with salt, black pepper and paprika as taste. Rub the slices with crushed garlic.Crack the eggs into a deep bowl and beat them with a fork. Season with a pinch of salt.Prepare an ovenproof dish for the casserole: grease the dish with 2 tablespoon oil.Preheat the oven to 160C / 320F.Dip the chicken breast slices in the beaten eggs, then coat the slices in the grated cheese. Line the chicken slices in the ovenproof dish.
Cut the zucchinis into 1 cm / 0,4 inches. Line the zucchini slices on top of the chicken breasts.
Mix the rest of the beaten eggs with the singe cream.
Pour the mixture on top of the zucchini.
Sprinkle the top of the casserole with the leftover cheese.
Place the casserole in the preheated oven and bake it for 25 minutes until the top is golden brown.
